## Required behaviors

### Startup
- On app load, check for a saved token.
- If a token exists, call `/api/v1/auth/me`.
- If valid, hydrate the protected app.
- If invalid, clear session and redirect to `/login`.

### Login
- Submit credentials to `POST /api/v1/auth/login`.
- Store the returned bearer token.
- Immediately call `GET /api/v1/auth/me`.
- Persist current user, memberships, roles, permissions, and active business context.
- Redirect to `/app/dashboard`.

### Business switching
- If the user has multiple memberships, render a business switch control.
- On switch, call `POST /api/v1/auth/switch-business`.
- Replace the stored token with the returned token.
- Re-run `GET /api/v1/auth/me`.
- Invalidate business-scoped data caches and refetch current pages.

### Data pages
- Render returned data defensively.
- Assume list shapes may stabilize later.
- Regenerate types whenever the live OpenAPI changes.

