## C. Current auth contract details

### `POST /api/v1/auth/login`

#### Request body
```json
{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "secret",
  "business_id": null
}
```

#### Example response
```json
{
  "access_token": "...",
  "token_type": "bearer",
  "business_id": "uuid",
  "user": {
    "id": "uuid",
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "is_active": true
  }
}
```

### Session hydration sequence
After login:
1. save `access_token`
2. call `GET /api/v1/auth/me`
3. store:
   - current user
   - active business id
   - memberships
   - roles
   - permissions
4. enter the protected app

### Business switch sequence
When membership count > 1:
1. call `POST /api/v1/auth/switch-business`
2. replace stored token
3. re-run `GET /api/v1/auth/me`
4. invalidate business-scoped caches
5. refetch list pages

