## D. Current error handling expectations

| Status | Meaning | Frontend requirement |
|---|---|---|
| 401 | unauthenticated / expired session | clear token and route to login |
| 403 | signed in but not authorized | show readable in-page denial |
| 422 | validation or request issue | show request/field feedback |
| 500 | backend error | show readable server error state |

### Important behavior notes
- Protected endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer <access_token>`.
- `POST /api/v1/bootstrap` is first-run only.
- Once initial users exist, bootstrap should return `403`.
- Permission failures must be visible and explicit.

